===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|crepen}}, from {{inh|en|ang|crēopan||to creep, crawl}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*kreupan}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*kreupaną||to twist, creep}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*grewbʰ-||to turn, wind}}. Cognate with {{cog|fy|krippe}}, {{m|fy|krûpe}}, {{cog|fy|crjippa||to creep}}, {{cog|nds|krepen}} and {{m|nds|krupen}}, {{cog|nl|kruipen||to creep, crawl}}, {{cog|gmh|kriefen||to creep}}, {{cog|da|krybe||to creep}}, {{cog|no|krype||to creep}}, {{cog|sv|krypa||to creep, crawl}}, {{cog|is|krjúpa||to stoop}}.

The noun is derived from the verb.

